summary: An ITC customer, whose wife works there, calls to change the address listed on the account, as well as to lodge a complaint about a frozen snack with a short shelf life. The customer is transferred multiple times within the company, and it is suggested that the complaint be given to a local agent to investigate. The customer is assured that the issue will be resolved and that they will be contacted with a resolution soon. The call ends with the customer being satisfied that their complaints have been heard and will be acted upon.
speaker_a_summary: Kyle needs assistance with a frozen app and auto pay on his account. He lives in house number 147/2, behind the Bombay Hotel in Mumbai, in the Naik Nagar district. He would like the issue resolved as soon as possible. The agent asks for a voucher and states they will look into the issue, but Kyle is unresponsive other than to insist on a same-day resolution. Kyle's number is the same as the communication number, and he has made other complaints within the internal system.
speaker_b_summary: The user is calling a customer service of a large Indian company ITC to solve a problem with one of their products. The product in question is a pack of frozen snacks with a bad smell which should be replaced. The customer wants to make sure that their home address is updated in the system and is then forwarded to the agent in charge of their complaint. The customer is advised to hand the product over to the agent for investigation and possible replacement. The customer is satisfied with the level of customer service provided by the company and expresses their satisfaction with the company's products in general, mentioning that they specifically like the ITC Master frozen snacks Crispy chicken fries. The call ends with the customer being provided with the contact details of the Pune branch of the company.
